{"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":0,"metadata":{"colab":{"provenance":[],"authorship_tag":"ABX9TyPFfleZW6v+jVNK49lNuagN"},"kernelspec":{"name":"python3","display_name":"Python 3"},"language_info":{"name":"python"}},"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"774a2ff7"},"source":["### DNA to Protein Translation Function\n","\n","This function will take a DNA sequence and translate it into a protein sequence. It uses the standard genetic code. It will start translation at the first start codon (AUG, which translates from DNA as ATG) and stop at a stop codon (TAA, TAG, TGA). If no start codon is found, it will return an empty string. If the sequence ends without a stop codon, it will translate what's available up to the end."]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"74fd9a06","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1763189594261,"user_tz":480,"elapsed":9,"user":{"displayName":"Saumi Saurin Shah","userId":"08664682234206450632"}},"outputId":"9cf65dd1-e0e3-479e-aeb2-8f19912cabc7"},"source":["def translate_dna_to_protein(dna_sequence):\n","    \"\"\"\n","    Translates a DNA sequence into a protein sequence.\n","\n","    Args:\n","        dna_sequence (str): The DNA sequence to translate (e.g., 'ATGCGTTAG').\n","\n","    Returns:\n","        str: The translated protein sequence.\n","    \"\"\"\n","    genetic_code = {\n","        'ATA':'I', 'ATC':'I', 'ATT':'I', 'ATG':'M',\n","        'ACA':'T', 'ACC':'T', 'ACG':'T', 'ACT':'T',\n","        'AAC':'N', 'AAT':'N', 'AAA':'K', 'AAG':'K',\n","        'AGC':'S', 'AGT':'S', 'AGA':'R', 'AGG':'R',\n","        'CTA':'L', 'CTC':'L', 'CTG':'L', 'CTT':'L',\n","        'CCA':'P', 'CCC':'P', 'CCG':'P', 'CCT':'P',\n","        'CAC':'H', 'CAT':'H', 'CAA':'Q', 'CAG':'Q',\n","        'CGA':'R', 'CGC':'R', 'CGG':'R', 'CGT':'R',\n","        'GTA':'V', 'GTC':'V', 'GTG':'V', 'GTT':'V',\n","        'GCA':'A', 'GCC':'A', 'GCG':'A', 'GCT':'A',\n","        'GAC':'D', 'GAT':'D', 'GAA':'E', 'GAG':'E',\n","        'GGA':'G', 'GGC':'G', 'GGG':'G', 'GGT':'G',\n","        'TCA':'S', 'TCC':'S', 'TCG':'S', 'TCT':'S',\n","        'TTC':'F', 'TTT':'F', 'TTA':'L', 'TTG':'L',\n","        'TAC':'Y', 'TAT':'Y', 'TAA':'_', 'TAG':'_',\n","        'TGC':'C', 'TGT':'C', 'TGA':'_', 'TGG':'W',\n","    }\n","\n","    protein = []\n","    dna_sequence = dna_sequence.upper() # Ensure uppercase\n","\n","\n","    start_codon_index = dna_sequence.find('ATG')\n","    if start_codon_index == -1:\n","        return \"\" # No start codon found\n","\n","    # Start translation from the start codon\n","    for i in range(start_codon_index, len(dna_sequence) - 2, 3):\n","        codon = dna_sequence[i:i+3]\n","        if codon in genetic_code:\n","            amino_acid = genetic_code[codon]\n","            if amino_acid == '_': # Stop codon\n","                break\n","            protein.append(amino_acid)\n","        else:\n","            # Handle invalid codons or end of sequence not divisible by 3\n","            break\n","\n","    return \"\".join(protein)\n","\n","\n","# Example usage:\n","dna_seq1 = \"ATGCGTTAGTTGACGTAG\"\n","protein1 = translate_dna_to_protein(dna_seq1)\n","print(f\"DNA Sequence 1: {dna_seq1}\")\n","print(f\"Protein Sequence 1: {protein1}\")\n","\n","dna_seq2 = \"GCATGCGTAGGTAGGA\"\n","protein2 = translate_dna_to_protein(dna_seq2)\n","print(f\"\\nDNA Sequence 2: {dna_seq2}\")\n","print(f\"Protein Sequence 2: {protein2}\")\n","\n"],"execution_count":5,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["DNA Sequence 1: ATGCGTTAGTTGACGTAG\n","Protein Sequence 1: MR\n","\n","DNA Sequence 2: GCATGCGTAGGTAGGA\n","Protein Sequence 2: MRR\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"8e6be611"},"source":["### Hamming Distance Function\n","\n","This function calculates the Hamming distance between two strings. The Hamming distance is the number of positions at which the corresponding symbols are different. This function will pad the shorter string with a specified character (defaulting to a space) to match the length of the longer string, if their lengths differ. This allows for comparison even when strings are of unequal length, which is a common requirement when applying the concept more broadly than its strict definition for equal-length strings."]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"b35b8ded","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1763189623937,"user_tz":480,"elapsed":14,"user":{"displayName":"Saumi Saurin Shah","userId":"08664682234206450632"}},"outputId":"47312bc6-a70a-48d8-eb65-9a5828273fdf"},"source":["def calculate_hamming_distance(str1, str2, pad_char=' '):\n","    \"\"\"\n","    Calculates the Hamming distance between two strings.\n","    If strings are of different lengths, the shorter string will be padded\n","    with 'pad_char' to match the length of the longer string.\n","\n","    Args:\n","        str1 (str): The first string.\n","        str2 (str): The second string.\n","        pad_char (str): The character to use for padding if lengths differ.\n","\n","    Returns:\n","        int: The Hamming distance between the two strings.\n","    \"\"\"\n","    len1 = len(str1)\n","    len2 = len(str2)\n","\n","    if len1 < len2:\n","        str1 = str1 + pad_char * (len2 - len1)\n","    elif len2 < len1:\n","        str2 = str2 + pad_char * (len1 - len2)\n","\n","    distance = 0\n","    for i in range(max(len1, len2)):\n","        if str1[i] != str2[i]:\n","            distance += 1\n","\n","    return distance\n","\n","# Example usage with your provided usernames:\n","slack_username = \"saumi_shah\"\n","twitter_handle = \"Saumi@99\"\n","\n","distance1 = calculate_hamming_distance(slack_username, twitter_handle)\n","print(f\"Slack Username: '{slack_username}'\")\n","print(f\"Twitter Handle: '{twitter_handle}'\")\n","print(f\"Hamming Distance: {distance1}\")\n","\n"],"execution_count":6,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Slack Username: 'saumi_shah'\n","Twitter Handle: 'Saumi@99'\n","Hamming Distance: 6\n"]}]}]}
